com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface MapEntry


  • public interface MapEntry
    An entry for a UPA Map that can house only other Container Types. Map is a uniform type, where the Map.containerType() indicates the single type housed in each entry. Each entry has an associated action which informs the user of how to apply the information contained in the entry.
    See Also:
    Map, MapEntryFlags, MapEntryActions

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears FieldEntry object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, FieldEntry object can be reused without using clear().

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter)
        Encode a single map entry with pre-encoded primitive key. Must be called after Map.encodeSetDefsComplete() and/or Map.encodeSummaryDataComplete(). Set encodedKey with pre-encoded data before calling this method. Typical use:
        1. Call Map.encodeInit()
        2. Call MapEntry.encode() for each map entry in the list using the same buffer
        3. Call Map.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeComplete

        int encodeComplete(EncodeIterator iter,
                   boolean success)
        Completes Map Entry encoding. Typical use:
        1. Call Map.encodeInit()
        2. Call MapEntry.encodeInit()..MapEntry.encodeComplete() for each map entry in the list using the same buffer
        3. Call Map.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        success - If true - successfully complete the aggregate, if false - remove the aggregate from the buffer.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • decode

        int decode(DecodeIterator iter,
           java.lang.Object keyData)
        Decode a single map entry.
        Parameters:
        iter - Decode iterator
        keyData - The decoded key data. If the user provides this pointer, this method will automatically decode the key to it(the pointer MUST point to memory large enough to contain the primitive that will be written).

      • action

        void action(int action)
        The entry action helps to manage change processing rules and tells the consumer how to apply the information contained in the entry. For specific information about possible action's associated with a MapEntry, see MapEntryActions. Must be in the range of 0 - 15.
        Parameters:
        action - the action to set

      • action

        int action()
        The entry action helps to manage change processing rules and tells the consumer how to apply the information contained in the entry. For specific information about possible action's associated with a MapEntry, see MapEntryActions.
        Returns:
        the action

        Returns:
        permData

      • encodedKey

        Buffer encodedKey()
        Encoded map entry key information. The encoded type of the key corresponds to the Map's keyPrimitiveType. The key value must be a base primitive type and cannot be blank, DataTypes.ARRAY, or DataTypes.UNKNOWN primitive types.
        Returns:
        encodedKey

      • encodedKey

        void encodedKey(Buffer encodedKey)
        Encoded map entry key information. The encoded type of the key corresponds to the Map's keyPrimitiveType. The key value must be a base primitive type and cannot be blank, DataTypes.ARRAY, or DataTypes.UNKNOWN primitive types.If populated on encode methods, this indicates that the key is pre-encoded and encKey will be copied while encoding.
        Parameters:
        encodedKey - the encodedKey to set

      • encodedData

        Buffer encodedData()
        The encoded content of this MapEntry.
        Returns:
        encodedData

      • encodedData

        void encodedData(Buffer encodedData)
        The encoded content of this MapEntry. If populated on encode methods, this indicates that data is pre-encoded, and encData will be copied while encoding.
        Parameters:
        encodedData - the encodedData to set
